column8:
For each pokemon, mark when you either have the pokemon or if you have its preevolution to evolve later. 

All pokemon should have the same OT where possible. Multiple playthroughs of some games are required.
column15: You should aim to get each pokemon from its origin game. If you don't have access to that game or unable to transfer up from that game, it is acceptable to use the Alternative Origin.
column17:
The green bars indicate where the 'mons go in the boxes. Bright Green means that pokemon is the first in its box. The Darker Green means it's the first in it's line.

For event-only pokemon, it is acceptable to use Powersaves devices or other exploits to insert the mystery gift into the game. Instructions have been linked where needed.
All pokemon that can gigantamax should be represented by that pokemon.
